3.Searching for Patterns
#Use grep to find all lines containing the word "root" in /etc/passwd.
@Payal1899 ➜ /etc $ cat passwd | grep root
root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash
@Payal1899 ➜ /etc $ 

4. Zipping and Unzipping
#Compress the test_dir directory into a file named test_dir.zip using zip.
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ zip test_dir.zip test_dir
  adding: test_dir/ (stored 0%)
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ ls
Assignment-1  test_dir  test_dir.zip

#Unzip test_dir.zip into a new directory named unzipped_dir.
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ ls
Assignment-1  test_dir  test_dir.zip
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ unzip test_dir.zip -d unzipped_dir
Archive:  test_dir.zip
   creating: unzipped_dir/test_dir/
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ ls
Assignment-1  test_dir  test_dir.zip  unzipped_dir
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ cd unzipped_dir/
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning/unzipped_dir (Assignment) $ ls
test_dir
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning/unzipped_dir (Assignment) $ 

