6. Changing Permissions
#Create a file named secure.txt
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ touch secure.txt
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ ls
Assignment-1  index.html  secure.txt  test_dir  test_dir.zip  unzipped_dir

#change its permissions to read-only for everyone using chmod.
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ chmod 444 secure.txt
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ ls -la secure.txt 
-r--r--r-- 1 codespace codespace 0 Mar 24 15:14 secure.txt
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ 


7. Working with Environment Variables
#Use export to set a new environment variable called MY_VAR with the value "Hello, Linux!".
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ export MY_VAR="Hello, Linux!"
@Payal1899 ➜ /workspaces/Devops-Learning (Assignment) $ printenv | grep MY_VAR
MY_VAR=Hello, Linux!

